title: Grateful Dead Live at Boutwell Auditorium on 1980-04-28
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, They Love Each Other, El Paso, Althea, Looks Like Rain, Tennessee Jed, Far From Me, Feel Like A Stranger, Deal

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Samson & Delilah, He's Gone-> The Other One-> Drums-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad

reviews.review_text:
great recording, show give this one a listen!  the recording has a lot of bottom end, and the show just rips.   Alabama getaway indeed!

the other one get kind of scary at the end, better hide the children for this one
Rich Recording Good show and very nice recording by Mr. Taylor. Nak 300s are very natural sounding mics.

My 1st show... The Other one was indeed scary! Thanks John G for guidance.

The show had great energy.

I sat way up front directly behind a taper with a huge Nak deck (it took something like 8 D cell batteries). Mason certainly could have been the taper.

It was a bit short, with GDTRFB encore for, iirc, Dan Healy who just lost his dad & was flying back after the show.
